{
  "name": "fix-remaining-gremlins-in-the-20260406-0429",
  "idea": "Fix remaining gremlins in the video-editor effect system: (1) validateAndCoerceParams drops extra params not in schema \u2014 start reduce with { ...params } so unrecognized params pass through while schema-defined ones get validated on top. (2) register() dedup uses reference equality for schema (existing.schema === schema) which fails when same schema is passed as new object \u2014 compare code only for dedup since schema doesn't change independently. (3) replaceEffectRegistry runs every render \u2014 guard with if check so it only writes when registry actually changes. (4) EffectLayerSequence wraps in unnecessary Sequence when startFrame is 0 \u2014 skip inner Sequence offset when from would be 0. Key files: effects/validateParams.ts, effects/DynamicEffectRegistry.ts, hooks/useEffectRegistry.ts, compositions/EffectLayerSequence.tsx, effects/DynamicEffectRegistry.test.tsx",
